newsitem.title: USA: FCOJ weekly movement rises to 6.146 mln gallons.
newsitem.headline: FCOJ weekly movement rises to 6.146 mln gallons.

text.p: The Florida Citrus Processors Association said frozen concentrated orange juice movement into trade channels for the week ended May 24 was 6,146,663 gallons compared with 4,911,368 gallons last week.
Imports were 768,758 gallons compared with 174,248 gallons the previous week. There were 27,147 domestic receipts for this week compared with 26,321 the previous week.
Retail movement was 1,001,322 gallons, while bulk movement was 4,601,984 gallons.
Current season cumulative movement was 132,813,134 gallons.
The final total pack for the season is 228,398,607 gallons.
